      "Name": "Realtime: Turn Moderator",
      "Description": "Room turn moderator for multi-agent realtime voice meetings. Run once per turn (a fast prompt, NOT an agent run): given the room roster + recent diarized conversation, returns the ordered agent(s) who should speak next (0+). Routes direct address and relevance, lets productive agent-to-agent discussion continue, and goes quiet on unproductive ping-pong. Bound to GPT-OSS-120B on Cerebras for low latency; swap the model binding (e.g. to Gemma on Cerebras) without code changes.",
